@flexiarg meta/exotype-determines-behaviour
@title Exotype Determines Behaviour
@sigils [🌏/甲 🔃/今]
@audience pattern users, mission designers, proof architects, AI collaborators
@tone foundational-analytic
@allow-new-claims false
@references [meta/designing-thoughts-not-text meta/layering-design-into-argument]
@keywords exotype, genotype, wiring diagram, context, underdetermination, specification, pattern, mission, proof

! conclusion:
  A design pattern's genotype (the structural move it prescribes) is
  underdetermined until the exotype (the environment it operates in) is
  specified. The wiring diagram is what pins the exotype. Without it,
  behaviour is designed in a vacuum and will drift from reality.

  + context: You are applying a pattern, designing a mission, or constructing a proof.
  + IF:
    A pattern says "in such-and-such a context, resolve the tension by doing X."
    The genotype (X) is clear. The context clause describes forces, constraints,
    and environmental conditions.

  + HOWEVER:
    The context clause is typically left implicit or described in prose. When the
    environment is not formally specified, the same genotype can produce different
    behaviours depending on which exotype it actually encounters — surfaces,
    timescales, constraint inputs, categories, conventions. The design is
    underdetermined relative to reality.

  + THEN:
    Specify the exotype explicitly before applying the genotype. In the futon
    ecosystem this means: write the wiring diagram (futon5) that names the ports,
    components, edges, timescales, and invariants the design must satisfy. In a
    proof this means: state the category, the conventions, and the hypotheses
    before invoking a theorem. In a mission this means: complete MAP (exotype
    discovery) before DERIVE (genotype design).

  + BECAUSE:
    When exotype is specified, the genotype's behaviour is determined — you can
    verify whether the pattern's resolution actually holds in the given
    environment. When exotype is missing, verification is impossible: the design
    may work in the designer's mental model but fail where it is deployed.

    Evidence across domains:
    - Software: Codex-over-IRC produced confabulation because the invoke contract
      had no exotype specification (no persistent job store, no evidence gate, no
      surface-independent execution truth). The genotype (invoke API + bridge relay)
      was built against an implicit exotype.
    - Proof: The universal triad (convention-bridge, hypothesis-category-check,
      compose-independent-lemmas) catches exactly the cases where a proof's
      genotype is underdetermined relative to its exotype — wrong category,
      unverified conventions, unproved composition steps.
    - Missions: The MAP phase exists to discover the exotype before DERIVE designs
      the genotype. Skip MAP and you design in a vacuum.

    The wiring diagram is the artifact that makes exotype explicit and checkable.
    A pattern without a wiring diagram is a suggestion. A pattern with a wiring
    diagram is a specification.

  + STATUS:
    status[ready]
    evidence[M-codex-irc-execution exotype gap; P3/P7/P8 rational reconstructions; futon5 wiring diagram formalism]

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Enforce wiring diagram existence as a mission checkpoint: no DERIVE without a wiring diagram that pins the exotype.]
    next[Cross-reference from math-strategy patterns (convention-bridge, hypothesis-category-check) which are instances of this meta-pattern.]
